In this Alchemy Gold Making Guide, I'll be
focusing on the Elixir Spec side of Alchemy.

00:00:16.269 --> 00:00:20.609
To get started you'll need to have Alchemy
leveled up decently and if you need help with

00:00:20.609 --> 00:00:26.579
that, I have all 1-525 leveling guides on
my website at tarouwowguides.com. It will

00:00:26.579 --> 00:00:30.821
also teach you how to get the Elixir Spec
if you're unsure. A good profession to go

00:00:30.821 --> 00:00:33.899
with Alchemy Elixir Spec is Herbalism.

00:00:33.899 --> 00:00:37.899
Alright, now that the initial prep is out
of the way, you can start banking with Elixir

00:00:37.899 --> 00:00:43.260
Alchemy. I like to start the day off getting
mats for whichever CD I plan to do. Today,

00:00:43.260 --> 00:00:47.969
I'm going with Living Elements but you could
also do Truegold or sell your cooldown in

00:00:47.969 --> 00:00:52.609
trade. As for which is better, take the sale
price minus the mats and do the one with the

00:00:52.609 --> 00:00:53.749
highest profit.

00:00:53.749 --> 00:00:59.179
Next, I start buying up mats for making flasks.
The best time to get mats is early morning

00:00:59.179 --> 00:01:04.559
to afternoon or on the weekends. This is usually
when they are the cheapest but monitor your

00:01:04.559 --> 00:01:09.310
server's Auction House to find out the best
time for you. It's also a good idea to watch

00:01:09.310 --> 00:01:15.280
trade chat for bulk sellers and to setup some
sort of CoD or direct trade deal with farmers

00:01:15.280 --> 00:01:20.049
if you can. Of course, if you already have
Herbalism, farm the mats yourself.

00:01:20.049 --> 00:01:24.759
Now that you've got some mats, you can start
making flasks and elixirs. The current proc

00:01:24.759 --> 00:01:31.560
rate is semi-low and the max is four extra
flasks or elixirs which will look like x5

00:01:31.560 --> 00:01:34.649
but you're already making one so it's really
four extra.

00:01:34.649 --> 00:01:41.250
The key to selling flasks and elixirs is timing.
6-8pm is peak time and as you can see here,

00:01:41.250 --> 00:01:48.110
sales started at around 5:30pm and were fairly
slow but by 6:50pm things started to pick

00:01:48.110 --> 00:01:54.770
up fast. By 7:22pm I started to run out of
flasks and looks like I also pissed someone

00:01:54.770 --> 00:01:59.880
off. Called a nerd by someone with the name,
"Knowledge", rofl. Oh noes.

